HEADWORD: Dan
<hw>Dan</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>dan</ets>,
<ets>danz</ets>, OF. <ets>danz</ets> (prop. only nom.), <ets>dan</ets>,
master, fr. L. <ets>dominus</ets>. See <er>Dame</er>.]</ety> <def>A
title of honor equivalent to <xex>master</xex>, or <xex>sir</xex>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Old <qex>Dan</qex> Geoffry, in gently spright⟦br⟧
The pure wellhead of poetry did dwell.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What time <qex>Dan</qex> Abraham left the Chaldee land.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dan</ent>⟦br⟧

